	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>278 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.15]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>LOL&nbsp;&nbsp;And thanks, I'm glad to hear we both help you out.<br><br>Don't worry, I don't think either of us will stop posting, and if you re-read I think you can see we're both trying to keep it toned down (no flames).  In reality Lunatic and I will never agree on the issue of what makes the best tank.  I understand his points, I just think that his tanking theories fit with Warriors in Boss MOB situations but don't fit into the smaller pick-up groups fighting under lvl 50 MOBs.<br><br>Lunatic focus' on the CHeal and on fights requiring alot of them when he talks about needing tons of HP's to tank.  I grew up fighting with few Clerics and mostly Druids and Shaman healing me.  I was so bad in an old Guild I was in I made a PLed a Cleric to 46 so he could support the Guild on Raids.  I have learned to maximize my value while reducing the use of the healer's mana as much as possible.  It only works in some zones, I spent 6 hours at 4 spawn in Velks with me a Necro and a Chanter one day.  We had no healer at all (well Necro's heal a little) and I was Tanking, not the pet, and we all lived.  I will contend a Warrior couldn't have done that, HPs made no difference at all that day.<br><br>But Luantic has some good points, I listen to what he posts too.  Just decide which one of us is saying things that work for you each time we disagree and listen to that advice for that question.<br><br>As to Dervs, I hated them, they hit to fast to cast around.  If you can fear them they drop fast, but once they start hitting you you have to get out of range and re-fear to live.  Tanking Dervs is a no-win situation, even at lvl 50 they hurt.  For Eastern Wastes there are 2 places to solo.  First is by the bridge, pull Kodiaks and Cougars there and fear them along the base.  The other place is Ulthorks along the Norther cliff.  Find the tree next to the spawn location and park pet there.  Pull anything blue to the tree, darkness and fear, they run right towards the Drawf Cooks hut so no adds once they get feared.  I did the bridge at 32-25, 35-40 was Ulthorks.<br><br>Neptunis</p>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 62 DE Gravelord<br>Have Axe, will travel</td></td></tr>
