	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=150995><span id= >Talupus</span></a><br><span id=notbold>48 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.10]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I am also very curious how you got your faction so high in two days. Please share. <br><br>I was using a 14/36 2hs before 20(for the lower dly) but had saved some money to buy a dark reaver from a guildmate. The second I dinged 20 I equiped the Reaver. Wiht 95str I constantly hit for the 40s. Big upgread from 29dmg... I would bet you have an Argent defender 33/49. Wiht 180str I would also bet you'll hit for the 60s lower 70s. I was soloing the giant fort in WW since lvl 22s new spells(AWESOME EXP Ill get into that later) Once I scored my 25th lvl I noticed I would hit for the upper 50s! Usually about 49 though.&nbsp;&nbsp;So at 25 I would say yer hitting for the 80s maybe 90s wiht your strength. Thats what I hit for at 37 with 123str.(LOL)<br><br><br>I would go to OT at your level. Make your way to the WW zone and pull MOBs to it. If you get in a jam just zone. This zone is exelent for soloing. As a newbie I did not know how to Fear kite so I just Tanked and lifetaped the mobs. I would usually coem out wiht 3/4 my life left. Med to 2 bubbles of mana and pull. Wiht gose pretty quick. It's safer to fear kite however, but requires the same downtime for mana. <br><br>At 22 move to WW Giant fort. Pull the Forest Giant Greens.(think thats it) Remeber to con here lvls vary quite a bit. Also kill low lvl Evergreens. I recomend camping the eastside by Cabilis. You can pull to the empty spot inbetween the two buildings. You can tank/tap or safer and can kill Yellow evergreens by fear kiting.  Pull them with Clinging darkness(CD). This uses less mana and rarely is resisted.(engulfing(ED) for evergreens)  Pull across bridge to road on east side of fort. By then the Giant should be at the door stand o nthe thrid lump in the road and wait to cast fear until they are wihtin range. The giant contunes to run and by the time fear is done casting the giant hits the dirt rode and keeps following it. Whack at it and recast fear/CD(ED) this is very safe And I never died all 9 Levels I was there! This requires a lot of mana downtime at 22 but at about 26 you can get away with having hardly any mana. Tank/tap worked for me but its highly unsafe if you don't have sow. I ran to cab for saftey by zoneing. But ogres looks like yer SOL or just run to OT tho is a little far. I fought here til  31 Killing everything Frest greens stop giving exp about 29 so you will have to kill em to get evergreens.<br><br>When now that my first book is written Ill continue to lvl and give out my words of wisdom/acid trip.<br><br>Islude-&quot;From the south. Heh, the deep south.&quot;<br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
