	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=153688><span id=Scholar>colinmarsh</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>61 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.15]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>an answer and a question...<br><br>you will hit hard at lvl 20. at lvl 35 with str. buffs ( 137 str. with proc on reaver) and a 20 dmg weapon i occasionally hit for 70 - more often in the 50's.<br><br>the luclin spells can be found in the echo caverns. once you enter the caverns through the false walls in shadowhaven you will walk by two guards, turn to the right and down a corridor which will dead end.<br><br>this dead end is a hidden door, if you click on the right side of it somewhere it will slide open. beyond that are a series of huts with merchants. one of them towards the back sells the new sk spells. <br><br>i think they are VERY useful. since the nerfing of disease counters, our ability to get aggro has been reduced. (can't use disease cloud anymore). but if you debuff each mob with scream of hate, scream of pain, siphon str. and despair. they will not like you much. usually a couple taunts will get them right on you. if not, hit them with darkness too. very mana intensive i know =( , but if you have to get one off a caster, this will usually work.<br><br>what did you kill the make yourself so liked by wood elves so quickly??<br><br>from 18 - 25 hunting. go to highhold pass right now. for the first few lvls 18 - 20. fight in an orc group near the kithicor zone. you will get great xp and raise your weapon skills. after a few lvls you will no longer be KOS to guards in high keep hold so you can bank and sell.<br><br>once you are 20 move into nearby high pass hold. get first in a goblin lookout group (first room) this is a good xp all the way to 25 when you may be able to get into a goblin warrior room camp - good xp all the way to 30. goblin camps usually require waiting but are worth it - bank in the zone, great xp, nice bronze and ringmail drops that sell well, good way to raise weapon skills.<br><br>only drawback is you will see ninja looting and you will often wait.<br><br>i'm not high enough lvl to know about planar stuff, sorry =)<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue May 28 12:47:18 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
