	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=153688><span id=Scholar>colinmarsh</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>61 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.15]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>i just completed the dark forge set a few weeks ago so i'm happy to give some tips.<br><br>minimum lvl to start this is definately 30. the invis and feign death will help. sadly it will be near impossible for you to acutally solo the crusaders.<br><br>you'll need a group to do this effectively, but you should be able to put one together for feeroot - it's great xp for lower 30's. kill all zealots, heralds, justicars and judicators. they are the main PH's for the crusaders.<br><br>i found the most consistent spawn spot for the crusaders to be the main ramp so i'd focus my attention there. with the main ramp you can pull so you never get more than two at a time so a group of three (even two if you are good) can keep them cleared.<br><br>the crusaders open each battle with a harm touch for about 330 pts of damage. you'll hear all sort of stats about sending pet in to take it, they do not always work and sadly the crusaders can &quot;throw&quot; harm touch froma distance. i was hit by it once when the mob was barely in bow distance.<br><br>few things to keep in mind...<br><br>1. once you get both pieces for a given piece of darkforge, go get the final pieces and finish it. you'll get lots of dupes and it helps to acquire pieces so you can pick up as much as possible<br><br>2. armor is lore!!!! if you have some in the bank or on you you cannot quest again to get 2nd piece. DON'T MAKE THE MISTAKE I MADE. transfer the completed piece to a friend and turn in prices to finish. only exception to this is the bracer.<br><br>3. pieces are multi-questable. i've done several of them with partners. make sure person who wants piece turns in final pieces to knight and that you are in a group when you do it.<br><br>4. MAKE SURE TO HAIL THE KNIGHT AND FIGURE OUT WHAT PIECES HE MAKES. don't make the mistake of turning in pieces to the wrong knight. if you go through the prompts each one will tell you what pieces he does. REDO THIS EVERYTIME YOU VISIT THEM THEY CAN CHANGE POSITIONS. dont' assume the knight on the left always does such and the knight on the right others. i've even seen times when only one knight was up. take the time to go through the chat and make sure. these pieces are hard to get.<br><br>5. find a druid or bard to help you out. they can track (maybe rangers too - dunno) and this is real helpful to know when crusaders are up.<br><br>6. SPEND TIME IN FEEROOT. even if you are not in a group. hang out in feeroot and try and find one. also i got one or two pieces from people killing crusaders and shouting decayed such and such on corpse. talk to high lvls in the area, they can help out by say single pulling a crusader off the top of a temple for you so you can fight it. most people are helpful if you are friendly. you can always solo certain lizards even in the low 30's and get xp. if you want to complete a set you need to spend time in feeroot. the groups will come. not as easy as OT or highkeep but possible.<br><br>if you have any specific questions as you go along, post here. i check in regularly and would love to help out a fellow knight.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue May 28 12:08:12 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
