	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>278 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.15]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Resistance is not a waste, but yours is still too low to expect complete resists.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>Until you get over 100 in any resistance you shouldn't expect frequent complete resists.  Even at 100 you will still not resist all spells of a type, and even at 200 you will still get hit by spells sometimes.  Remember that the Caster's level is also a factor, so while you will probably now resist most spells from green stuff, anything red to you will land their spells most times even with 100 resist.<br><br>Keep collecting the resistance gear.  At lvl 45 or so you'll want 150 sv magic and cold if you want to fight Vox, and Magic and Fire if you fight Naggy.  Even then you'll get hit with fears and their AE spells.<br><br>Good luck.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 55 DE Revenant</p>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 62 DE Gravelord<br>Have Axe, will travel</td></td></tr>
