	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=153688><span id=Scholar>colinmarsh</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>61 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.70]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>well i'm not sure this is true or not, but i was given a very high lvl dex. buff by an enchanter friend of mine once.<br><br>had no idea how much effect it would have. i must have raised my skill points by 10 in a half hour - no exaggeration. it was an uber buff no doubt but any buff that raises dexterity helps IMMENSELY.<br><br>one other suggestion I have is to carry multiple weapons and make a hotkey swap weapon slot on your main screen. that way you can toggle between weapons in the middle of&nbsp;&nbsp;a fight real easily.<br><br>i have found that when fighting yellow and white mobs the skills seems to rise faster. i could be wrong on this, but it sure seems that way. so when in a group in a dungeon fighting tough mobs, use your main weapon when you're not sure of the outcome of the fight but in the cases where you are or towards the end of a fight say, switch weapons.<br><br>i have done this for many lvls and it has enabled me to keep all 5 combat skills within 10 pts of the max of my lvl.<br><br>of course i should also point out that the only way i intially got all of them maxed was to draw a line in the sand at lvl 14 and say, i will not reach 15 until all five combat abilities are at 75.<br><br>i was lvl 14 for just about two days short of eternity, but it was kind of liberating. at times i'd just rush white mobs and hack away with a weapon i wasn't good with. sometimes i'd raise it 2 or 3 pts before dieing, but i didn't care that i died. i also found very efficient ways to kill myself. my bind spot was still the newbie nektulos spot at the time (i didn't learn about bind affinity until about lvl 20 - 1st character you see), so i'd just rush up to Dragoon X'Lotti and punch him - whack dead.<br><br>the funniest part was the reaction of people around me. &quot;umm guy, you're not going to ever win that fight, stop trying.&quot;<br><br>eventually they all reached 75 and ever since i've worked diligently to keep them up. it was painful but i just like knowing i can do anything with any weapon ;)<br><br>in case anyone is curious. i was NOT hardcore enough to raise hand to hand in this way. i'm ROFL just thinking about that. man then i would have gotten some comments. &quot;hey, monk can you pull for us?&quot; , &quot;Cool, dark elves can be monks now.&quot; , &quot;I didn't know monks wore banded&quot;</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
