't hard to hit the attack button &amp; stand there &amp; pray that the CH rotation works well enough to keep you alive (for the most part).  It has nothing to do with damage output or anything--it's all about taking damage.<br><br>Perhaps that is where the BS notion that SKs/PLDs can't tank came from--high end raids.  I'm not sure.<br><br>What I am sure about is that you (anyone) are fooling yourself big time if you think that a SK or PLD can tank substantially as well as a WAR (all things substantially equal).  Many of the people that play this game are not stupid &amp; they also know that.  Hence, WAR are typically at the front doing their thing, while we are generally viewed as just another melee--a damage producer if you will.  Well, if I wanted that, I would have played a ROG or a RGR to begin with.<br><br>I do, however, very much enjoy playing an SK, but there are some glaring errors, this probably being the biggest by a country mile....<br><br>I am interested, however, in what exactly you mean when you say that an SK can tank &quot;if played very well.&quot;  Please define what &quot;very well&quot; means.  What &amp; the timing of our spells is what Im guessing that you are primarily referring to.  Otherwise, we are just an underpowered WAR.<br><br>To me, tanking is all about taking damage.  You want the MOB on you &amp; you need to be able to take the damage that he's gonna give you.  Now, whatever venue we get there is fine, but, at the end of the day, its ALL ABOUT HP, either having enough to stand there or having the AC to reduce the amount of damage done to you; it makes no difference to me how you get there, but its all about HP.<br><br>That being said, and the fact that the spells are what make SKs harder than WAR, lets take a look at the spells available to an SK at 55 that will aid an SK in tanking (as defined above &amp; primarily the best ones--note that I am NOT focusing on damage--I do NOT recognize that as a primary &quot;TANKING&quot; attribute):<br><br>Shroud of Pain (18 AC tap)<br>Shroud of Death (~50 procing lifetap)<br>Spirit Tap (150 lifetap)<br>Abduction of Strength (indirectly related, as it reduces MOB STR by 25, thereby reducing damage done)<br>Torrent of Hate (35 ATK debuff, again reduces damage done)<br><br>Torrent of Pain (AC tap) is available at 56, as well as a decent skin (about 230pts), but those aren&amp;#8217;t available at 55.<br><br>That&amp;#8217;s substantially it.  In a typical fight, you can generally land AoS, SoP, &amp; ToH really fast &amp; early, so those aren&amp;#8217;t really an issue.  So, from what I can see, you are primarily talking about the timing &amp; use of Spirit Tap as to what makes our class challenging to play/tank as an SK?  If Im wrong, then please do tell.  If Im not, then I am forced to disagree with you&amp;#8212;that spell isn&amp;#8217;t going to save you from much, nor is there a lot of strategy behind using it (ok&amp;#8212;there is a little as far as timing the cast, but that is a skill you learn VERY early as an SK, especially when channeling skill is low).<br><br>Verant needs to wake up &amp; smell the coffee&amp;#8212;SKs &amp; PLDs should be able to tank better than they presently do.  I dont care how they get there&amp;#8212;mine was just a silly example of how to do it.  And yes, if they made the changes I am referring to, the class would STILL be very challenging to play&amp;#8212;PERHAPS even MORESO&amp;#8230;.<br><br>Lunatic<br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
