	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=153688><span id=Scholar>colinmarsh</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>61 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.15]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>i fully agree with cannis. ac is king for sk's, especially if you plan to try soloing.<br><br>at your lvl i would suggest the following for raising cash to get items and it's great for xp too.<br><br>go to highhold pass and get in an orc group. you'll be able to get great xp right to lvl 20 when you'll want to head home to train up double attack.<br><br>while fighting orcs you'll get LOTS of ringmail drops which sell for good pp. you'll also raise your faction to where the guards there won't attack you and the merchants are always indiff so you can sell easy.<br><br>then once 20 go back to highhold but go into the keep and get in a goblin lookout room group. great xp. and lots of bronze armor and fine steel drops. both can be sold to vendors and you can even auction bronze with a little patience.<br><br>note that both these camp spots are crowded , but for a reason. they're great for loot and xp. so talk to the leader get on the waiting list - it's usually not too bad since luclin and it will be worth it at your lvl i think.<br><br>don't fall into that LOIO trap that everyone seems to ;)</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
