	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, May 18th 2:16 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85776><span id=Sage>Cannis</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>686 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.15]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>At 49th I use the fear method for breaking the Lantern in CoM when I solo. I pull the mobs to the zone line fear one, then the mob that is still on me I Darkness Fear and when the other fear breaks I just fear it again. When the fear breaks on the mob I am fighting I run back to the zone line re apply darkness fear again that second darkness and fear will let me kill it before it fades. The other mob will come back I should still be at half my mana and I will darkness and fear till dead just make sure you don't follow the mob more than a quarter way on the bridge or the ones through the gate will add, just run back to zone line and start your fear kite again. After you break lantern you can just single pull the 3 spawn at through the gate just make sure as your facing them you pull from your right to left. I med to full and fight with half to 3/4 health as a DESK. I life tap the last part bub of health till dead.<br><br>My gear for my level is average so any Sk could do the same thing. <br><br>Gear I am using is:<br>2 cougar claws<br>2 Jagged Bands<br>Ry'Gorr Coif (don't want helm graphic)<br>Visor of Dreaded Gaze<br>Coterie Generals Cloak<br>Spider Fur Collar/Belt<br>Tree Weave<br>Kylong Greaves<br>Blood Ember Arms<br>Sentient Gauntlets<br>Clay Guardian Shield<br>Noct Blade/Ebon Mace<br>or Runed Frost Blade<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Cannis 65th Ranger<br></td></td></tr>
