	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=5&mid=102155476519578>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102155476519578>RE: Need some advice from Exp EQ players.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102155476519578#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, May 16th 9:21 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>278 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well the good news is you are better equiped than I was at lvl 11.&nbsp;&nbsp;The bad news is that 12 plat won't buy much.<br><br>What you could upgrade for 12pp is basically your weapon.  If you get either a Velium 2h Sword for about 5pp or a Frozen 2h Sword for a little more you would then be able to kill wilowisps which is where non-twinks make their money at lvl 12-20.  Each greater lightstone will bring in 9plat once you trade them in to the gypsie in S Ro and then sell back the research box, you'll get xp too.<br><br>Other stuff you might be able to get:<br><br>Bloodstained Mantle 6AC +STR +10 sv Magic, allows you to bash those wisps since it's magic.<br><br>Straw Spun Belt 10AC belt, very nice for AC<br><br>Velium Round Shield, maybe, nice AC, sv cold and again lets you bash magic stuff.<br><br>There are a few places now where you could make some money.  First kill Skels and sell bone chips to those needy Necro's.  Next is wil-o-wisps in the commons, as already stated greater lightstones are good money, lightstones are also almost a plat per to a merchant.  If you want to work faction with Nariak, go into Nektalos Forest and turn left to the SW corner and start killing the Halfling Raiders (watch out for the deputy and the medic, both alot higher level).  Save the hats and beads they drop, they are quest stuff.  These guys drop alot of bronze weapons and the hats get turned in to give you a 2hs weapon a little bit better than fine steel.  Or if your server is like mine (I don't play pvp) you could get into a derv group in either the Commons or S Ro, as the Derves also drop alot of bronze weapons and the rings they drop are ok money too.<br><br>Maybe the new Newbie Quests for armor will give you some upgrades, check them out.  They are all Race/Class specific and I never had them available when I was that level so know nothing about them.<br><br>Just some random ideas of what you can do.  Once you get some money (100pp+) you can start looking for things like Jagged Bands, Grotesk Alloy Mask, Khobold Hide Boots (low AC but cheapest kick magic item I know) and maybe an agility neck piece to get you over 75 AGI.<br><br>Good luck.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 55 DE Revenant</p>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 62 DE Gravelord<br>Have Axe, will travel</td></td></tr>
