	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=5&mid=10213347526904>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=10213347526904>RE: Solo Fear Kiting - Best Spots</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=10213347526904#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, May 13th 8:14 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>305 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.75]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Although I was substantially grouped thoughout my 30s &amp; 40s, when I did solo in my 30s, I did it in the Overthere.&nbsp;&nbsp;The best spot I could find was IN THE &quot;ALLEY&quot; TO FRONTIER MOUNTAINS.  You try to solo on the road or anywhere near the ledge, fort, etc., you are most likely going to have adds (the worst of which would be a goon) and that you do NOT want.<br><br>The alley, however, is a great spot to solo (that I found).  You can easily zone, the MOB has a very predictable pathing, and you can smack him with a few DOTs (Heart Flutter, Heat Blood) as he is coming after you (this is assuming that you pulled him with Engulfing Darkness).  <br><br>The trick, however, is to land fear at as close as possible, but prior to, it wearing off.  I didnt nearly have the problem of timing darkness as I did fear, but that may just be the way that I soloed.<br><br>The drawback of soloing in the alley is that when the goons come crusing, peeps run down the alley all the time to zone to avoid the goon(s), which can train you or whatever.  That, however, was easily noticable, as everyone shouts GOON as soon as one shows up.<br><br>Not sure if this helps any, but I hope so<br><br>Lunatic</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
