	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=5&mid=102189952839947>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102189952839947>RE: The Death of Disease Cloud</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102189952839947#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, May 20th 9:08 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>278 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.15]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Ok I'm starting a new reply thread here to get back near the top and give us more hrozantal space so posts don't streach out so much.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am in no way discounting what you guys are saying, I'm just adding another real EQ experiance for agro management to give people some idea what the disease cloud change means.<br><br>I spent yesterday in Griegs End, Luclin Zone.  MOBs went from green to me to yellow to lvl 60's (we left those alone as well as leaving Grieg himself alone although he kept showing up).  My Guild decided to explore it, starting at 1 end and fighting through as much of the zone as we could from 1 end to the other.  We had 8 people total, 2 groups of 4, lots of Druids, 1 lvl 60 Warrior, 1 lvl 60 Wizard, 1 Cleric and just me as the other tank.  Spells in this zone have standard resists, nothing was immune (except some to changes in speed), nothing had excessive agro on any 1 spell we have as happens sometimes in other zones.  Also MOBs are normal for their agro too, you can pull MOBs past people unlike CoM for example.<br><br>Agro was never a problem, and we had a horrible time with LD all day.  When Main Tank went LD I'd just drop Heart Flutter or Shroud of Pain on the MOB and I had agro.  I always start a fight de-buffing them (Torrent of Hate and Shroud of Pain) the drop Boil Blood on the ones that were high blue and would live long enough for the dot to work.  So basically I had good agro before anything bad happened.  IF I tried to add Heart Fluter while the Tank was still fighting, I got agro'd and would have to turn off auto-attack to let Warrior take it back.  With adds I'd lead with Shroud of Pain and the Heart Flutter to ensure agro if the MOB was not going to be mezzed (we had a Bard too).  We survived several waves of MOBs like this some times (they will sometimes spawn in groups of 3-4 and respawn on the same spot quickly if you don't move, traps maybe).  <br><br>I was in no way Agro handicapped by not having Disease Cloud in my line-up.  I didn't even have to use Shadow Vortex for agro, by keeping some of the more powerful debuffs and dot's on MOBs at all times I was always high enough on the agro list that I could grab agro anytime by hitting the MOB with Shoud of Pain and the Taunt key.  I was also using a 2hs, when I switched in the Ebon Mace and SBS to take while waiting for the Warrior to get back on-line, I had an even easier time holding agro.  Oh yeh, we were moving all the time except when waiting on someone who was LD, and I never went OOM.  It's not an overly crowded zone for MOBs and we had to move to find them so it wasn't non-stop pulls, but you can keep agro still without burning all your mana (I fight at 164 INT btw so you can compare).<br><br>The change in Disease Cloud may be inconvienient, but it doesn't threaten our &quot;Class Defining&quot; ability.  So instead of complaining about the change I for 1 will continue to post the other tactics that work for me to keep agro and hope the rest of you will too so that others can learn.  And since some people will contradict my methods (as they should if they have a better idea) I'll post zone and MOB info so you have something to work with to disagree.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 55 DE REvenant</p>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 62 DE Gravelord<br>Have Axe, will travel</td></td></tr>
