	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>278 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.10]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>First YAY!!!, I can finally relagate Desease Cloud to the back of the spell book where it has always belonged!<br><br>Next YAY, I can use my Dark Spear of Venom while not being the Main Tank again, it no longer out agro's the Frostbringer's proc.&nbsp;&nbsp;It has some nice saves, with a good ratio and the proc, Sicken, is great when no grouped with a Shaman, so I like to use it to keep piercing skills up.<br><br>But ok, back to the taunt thing.  I have rarely used Desease Cloud for taunt, but kept it memmed when I was backup Tank so I could brag quick agro when needed (adds or Cleric starting to take hits).  Otherwise I use Torrent of Hate and Shroud of Pain all the time, but have to be very careful I don't pull agro off Main Tanks using them both.  SO, with 2 very fast casting, low mana spells that actually give real benefits I can create more agro that I normally want.  I didn't use Shadow Vortex alot as it over-agro's both of the other debuffs I use.  Now Shadow Vortex has gone back into use, and I LOVE what it does for my AC during fights.<br><br>My advice, when you are Main Tank either Darkness or cast Shadow Vortex on pulls as the MOB is inbound.  If you are pulling as well pull with Darkness and then stop and stack all your debuffs on the MOB as you bring it back to the group.  Yopu will have no trouble at all keeping agro after that.  If you are back-up Tank and need to get something off the Chanter fast use Shadow Vortex with a Bash/Slam, stunning a MOB really upsets them for some reason.  If you keep the MOB debuffed, carefully so as not to draw agro from the Main Tank, you should be high enough on the hate list to pull it quickly to you when needed with either Shadow Vortex or Heart Flutter (which out taunted Desease Cloud in most higher level zones but is just much slower cast time).<br><br>So now Shadowknights, we must adapt and move forward.  No complaining, sulking about or self doubting, we still rule the Agro by alot, we just have to use more of our skills to do it.  Let those weak Pali's rely on a lowbie spell for agro, we will do more damage and be more useful now while still keeping the agro away from them.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 55 DE Revenant</p>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 62 DE Gravelord<br>Have Axe, will travel</td></td></tr>
