	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=631><span id=Guru>Sir Parttime</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>142 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Greetings...<br><br>I humbly disagree with you on a number of different issues.&nbsp;&nbsp;First, just because a spell is of a low level does not mean that it is a useless spell.  I'm not sure you will ever hear a caster say that bind affinity, SoW or Gate/Port is useless and they are fairly low level spells.<br><br>Secondly, when I am in a group, my job..unless I am MT...is to keep an eye on all the caster types, especially clerics, enchanters, and wisards to make sure that nothing beats on them for any length of time.  Disease Cloud(1.5 sec. Cast/Mana 10/Recast=6 sec. + no buff counter) was a much better, less mana intensive method of taunting then the two spells you have mentioned (Torrent of Hate = 1.5 sec/Mana 60/Recast 6 sec  Shroud of Pain = 3 sec./Mana 100/Recast 6 sec.)<br><br>When I am main tank...once I have aggro, the wisards, clerics and other assundry magic types can cast with impunity (mostly) because of this fast, low mana spell.<br><br>Mana intensive spells can cause you to have to med. much more frequently and if pulls are coming quickly, you may not have the time.  And the number of buffs that you have may not be an issue in experience groups, but I'm betting you will miss the shammy or cleric buffs that Torrent and Shroud will overwrite in a raid situation.  (And from what I have read...it seems that the Torrent line of spells really don't generate that much aggro.)<br><br>Shadow Vortex is a slightly different issue...it is a good aggro gaining spell, but again mana and buff slots are an issue.  The one good thing that SV had over DC is of course DC is a DoT, making it unuseful if you want to re-mez a mob.<br><br>Darkness is a good spell as well...If it sticks, which I find to be about 2-5.<br><br>You mentioned pulling as well.  I'm thinking that if you are stoping to debuff mobs on the way in, that you are a fairly slow puller due to extended time having to med even if you are a Dark Elf.<br><br>You are correct that many of our other spells can fill in where DC left off.  SV and Heart Flutter are good choices.  However, those are both level 39 spells.  What is the level 17 SK going to use to save the life of his shammy, rogue, monk, or cleric hunting partner?  <br><br>And I sincerely doubt that you will be able to taunt off a Pally who uses those &quot;lowbie spell for agro&quot; if they don't want you too.  (Losing aggro to a Pally is very annoying...especially when you can't get it back.)<br><br>And lastly, I have no problem with dealing with adversity.  Shadowknights have been dealing with challanges since they picked up a sword.  (I still remember the 20% hybrid experience modifier)However, I do get annoyed by Verant &quot;fixing&quot; a problem, but being completely unaware that they were causing another, especially when that problem is a class defining ability.<br><br>Good hunting all...see ya in Norrath.</p>&nbsp;<br>Shrikke - Knight of Fear<br>Bristlebane</td></td></tr>
