	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>278 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.73]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Agility below 75 gives an AC penalty, so that's the first place to start.&nbsp;&nbsp;After that AGI will improve, slightly, your defensive skills, dodge, parry, rippost and help you learn them faster.<br><br>It's not a stat I spend alot of time on, but when Raiding I always get the buffs for it.  As a rule I try not to wear anything that's no AC except for Raids on AE Dragons where you have to wear resist jewelry.  In fact I perfer the Dropped Haste Belt form POA over the Sash of the Dragonborn I have as the 8AC +STR outweighs the extra Haste with only 2AC no stats on the sash for most fights (in my opinion).<br><br>Unless you are playing a character with very high starting Agility you may not see a big pay-off going with Agility items later on.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 55 DE Revenant</p>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 62 DE Gravelord<br>Have Axe, will travel</td></td></tr>
